Occurrences 2 and 4 — inside loops (~lines 104-109 and ~228-232):
  The loop triggers 3 hot reloads. Each iteration must complete before the next trigger. The current code does this by awaiting waitForLog each iteration. With the fix:
  BEFORE (per iteration):
    mcpServer.logs.length = 0;
    mcpServer.triggerHotReload();
    await waitForLog(mcpServer, 'plugin(s) mapped', 20_000);
  AFTER (per iteration):
    const mappedBefore = mcpServer.logs.filter(l => l.includes('plugin(s) mapped')).length;
    mcpServer.triggerHotReload();
    await waitFor(() => mcpServer.logs.filter(l => l.includes('plugin(s) mapped')).length > mappedBefore, 20_000, 200, 'plugin(s) mapped');
  The count-snapshot approach inherently ensures sequential waiting since each iteration captures the current count.

Occurrence 3 (~line 186) — standalone:
  Same pattern as occurrence 1.

Constraints:
- Use the existing `waitFor` helper from e2e/helpers.ts.
- Each occurrence needs a unique counter variable name within its scope.
- Do NOT change loop structure, assertions, or surrounding test logic.
- In loop contexts, the counter variable can be declared inside the loop body (it's a new scope each iteration).

